summary: "As a result, they did everything they could to weaken the central state and it’s ability to raise/maintain an army and have any...
question: "As a result, they did everything they could to weaken the central state and it’s ability to raise/maintain an army and have any sort of authority to intervene on member worlds. " This assessment is not correct when it comes to Princess Leia though as while she was indeed a proponent for not centralizing too much political power she was an outspoken opponent of military disarmament and the weakening of the New Republic Navy and warned that the Imperial Remnant factions are still a threat.
answer:
(cont) Wasn’t Leia sidelined in the NR Senate and denounced as “warmonger” specifically because she lobbied for more spending on defense and for the NR as a whole to take a more interventionist stance? Leia’s opposition was against the centralizing of executive power to prevent another Palpatine, but not against a strong military to keep the galaxy safe. After the signing of the Galactic Concordance she was among those who vehemently opposed the disarmament policies that were brought in.             

I stand corrected. When you put it that way, it makes sense that she’d go and form her own private army. In her experience, trying to correct things via political power does very little. Her father’s efforts to check the political power of Palpatine, first in the Republic Senate and then in the Imperial, came to naught. Her own efforts in the New Republic were similarly useless. On the other hand, violent revolution got shit done.

summary: Black Squadron - Chapter 20 - Azalea Scroggs - Star Wars - All Media Types [Archive of Our Own]
title: Black Squadron - Chapter 20 - Azalea Scroggs - Star Wars - All Media Types [Archive of Our Own]
excerpt: An Archive of Our Own, a project of the Organization for Transformative Works
description:
Luke nodded.

“Now we just hope they don’t have anti-aircraft weapons,” he muttered.

“Primary analyses have not detected any. If we are mistaken, then they will naturally be your primary targets.”

Luke smiled, their casual dialogue reminding him of their training sessions. It was so easy to exchange like this…

Qorl’s whisper immediately made him regret it.

“And a bootlicker at that.”

Luke rolled his eyes, and had to bite his tongue not to answer.
